# Performance Optimizations Walkthrough

This document outlines the performance improvements made to the UK Property Analyzer to reduce latency and improve perceived load times.

## 1. Parallelized Plot Size API Calls

### The Problem
Previously, the main `/api/analyze` route fetched property details from Rightmove and then *sequentially* waited for the PropertyData API to return the plot size (`getPlotSizeAcres`). Because PropertyData lookups can take 1-3 seconds, this delayed the initial render of the property on the frontend.

### The Solution
We removed the blocking `getPlotSizeAcres` call from `/api/analyze`. Instead, we moved this logic to `/api/market-data`, which the frontend already fetches asynchronously in the background.

**Changes:**
- Removed sequential blocking in `src/app/api/analyze/route.ts`.
- Wired `getPlotSizeAcres` into the concurrent `Promise.allSettled` block inside `src/lib/propertydata/market-data.ts`.
- Updated `PropertyZenView.tsx` to read `plotSizeAcres` from `property.marketData.data.ownership.plotSizeAcres` instead of `property.plotSizeAcres`.

**Result:**
The initial property analysis (price, images, core details) now returns significantly faster, improving the Time to First Byte (TTFB) and perceived performance. The plot size streams in alongside other market data.

