## 3. Application Data Flow Architecture

The following sequence diagram illustrates the complete flow of data when a user analyzes a new property via a Rightmove URL. It highlights the initial web scrape, the parallel API enrichments, and the final persistence layer.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    
    actor User
    participant UI as React Frontend (page.tsx)
    participant AnalyzeAPI as /api/analyze (Next.js API)
    participant Scraper as Rightmove Scraper
    participant API as Ext APIs (PropertyData / Google / Locrating)
    participant DB as SQLite DB (SavedProperty)
    
    User->>UI: Enter Rightmove URL & submit
    UI->>AnalyzeAPI: POST /api/analyze { url }
    
    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note right of AnalyzeAPI: Phase 1: Core Property Extraction
        AnalyzeAPI->>Scraper: Fetch HTML
        Scraper-->>AnalyzeAPI: Raw HTML
        AnalyzeAPI->>AnalyzeAPI: Extract Core Data (Price, Beds, Postcode, Images)
        AnalyzeAPI->>API: Google Geocoding (Postcode -> Lat/Lng)
        API-->>AnalyzeAPI: Coordinates
        AnalyzeAPI->>API: Google Places (Nearby Tubes/Trains)
        API-->>AnalyzeAPI: Nearest Stations
        AnalyzeAPI-->>UI: Return Initial Property JSON
    end
    
    UI->>UI: Render Core Property UI & Images
    
    rect rgb(255, 245, 238)
        Note right of UI: Phase 2: Parallel Async Enrichments
        
        par Market Data Fetch
            UI->>+AnalyzeAPI: POST /api/market-data
            AnalyzeAPI->>API: PropertyData APIs (Prices, Crime, Growth, Plot)
            API-->>AnalyzeAPI: Enrichment Data
            AnalyzeAPI-->>-UI: MarketDataResult JSON
            UI->>UI: Render Market Insights
        and Schools Fetch
            UI->>+AnalyzeAPI: POST /api/schools
            AnalyzeAPI->>API: Locrating API
            API-->>AnalyzeAPI: Attended Schools Data
            AnalyzeAPI-->>-UI: AttendedSchoolsResult JSON
            UI->>UI: Render Schools UI
        and Commute Times Fetch
            UI->>+AnalyzeAPI: GET /api/commute
            AnalyzeAPI->>API: Google Distance Matrix API
            API-->>AnalyzeAPI: Benchmark Durations
            AnalyzeAPI-->>-UI: CommuteTimes JSON array
            UI->>UI: Render Commute UI
        end
    end
    
    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note right of UI: Phase 3: Persisting State
        UI->>AnalyzeAPI: POST /api/saved-properties { property, market, schools, commute }
        AnalyzeAPI->>DB: prisma.savedProperty.upsert
        Note over DB: Data is stringified to JSON<br/>and stored in text columns
        DB-->>AnalyzeAPI: Success Output
        AnalyzeAPI-->>UI: 200 OK
    end
    
    Note over UI, DB: Next time property is loaded from sidebar, UI fetches directly from DB,<br/>bypassing Scraper and Ext APIs completely.
```
